      "raw_response": "{\n  \"final_bugs\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"The algorithm uses three nested loops (over c, j2 and j1) giving O(k\u00b7n\u00b2) time. With n up to 2000 and k up to n this can be up to ~4\u00b710\u2079 operations, far exceeding the time limit and causing a timeout on large test cases.\",\n      \"triggering_input\": \"1\\n2000 2000\\n\" + \" \".join(str(i) for i in range(1, 2001)) + \"\\n\",\n      \"fix\": \"Replace the DP with an O(n log n) solution based on the observation that the feasibility condition d2 - d1 \u2264 i2 - i1 - 1 is equivalent to a2 > a1. Keep only positions where i \u2265 a_i, then compute the longest strictly increasing subsequence (LIS) of their a_i values. If the LIS length is at least k, the minimal number of deletions equals the smallest d = i - a_i among the k\u2011th element of such a subsequence; otherwise output -1. This runs in O(n log n) and satisfies the constraints.\",\n      \"confirmed\": true,\n      \"reasoning\": \"The original DP is unnecessarily complex and too slow. The mathematical simplification shows that we only need a strictly increasing sequence of a_i among indices with i \u2265 a_i, which can be solved efficiently with LIS. Implementing this fix eliminates the timeout while preserving correctness.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}",
